---
import PageLayout from "@layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import TopLayout from "@layouts/TopLayout.astro";
import BottomLayout from "@layouts/BottomLayout.astro";
import { WORLDVIEWS } from "@consts";

const forestCards = [
  {
    title: "The Stormwood",
    theme: "Sensationalism",
    tagline: "Where intensity substitutes for depth.",
    description:
      "This forest is alive with movement. God feels near. Everything feels urgent. Stillness, however, can begin to feel like absence, and silence like danger.",
    href: "/forests/sensationalism",
  },
  {
    title: "The Closed Sky",
    theme: "Naturalism",
    tagline: "Where meaning must be manufactured.",
    description:
      "In this forest, nothing seems to break in from above. What cannot be measured starts to feel difficult to trust. Control feels responsible. Anxiety feels rational.",
    href: "/forests/naturalism",
  },
  {
    title: "The Shifting Grove",
    theme: "Moral Relativism",
    tagline: "Where safety starts to outrun truth.",
    description:
      "Here, sincerity carries moral weight. Harmony feels merciful. The ground shifts with the emotional weather, and disagreement can start to feel like threat.",
    href: "/forests/moral-relativism",
  },
  {
    title: "The Ironwood",
    theme: "Religion",
    tagline: "Where rules begin to crowd out discernment.",
    description:
      "In this forest, holiness is often measured by compliance. The system feels safe, questions can feel suspect, and control begins to sound like faithfulness.",
    href: "/forests/religion",
  },
];
---

<PageLayout
  title={WORLDVIEWS.TITLE}
  description={WORLDVIEWS.DESCRIPTION}
  image="/the-forests-og.png"
  schemaType="CollectionPage"
  section="The Forests"
>
  <TopLayout>
    <div class="animate space-y-6">
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-black dark:text-white mt-2">
          The Forests
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-2 text-lg italic text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
          Worldviews are not just ideas. They are environments.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-3 text-base text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
        <p>
          Long before we choose what we believe, we learn how the world works by
          breathing its air.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every forest has a climate. Every climate trains instincts. Every
          instinct shapes fruit.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Forests try to name the environments that quietly form us,
          including the ones that feel reasonable, spiritual, or protective.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </TopLayout>
  <BottomLayout>
    <div class="animate space-y-12">
      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black dark:text-white">
          How to Read the Forests
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-base text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
          <p>Forests are not merely sets of ideas. They are places people learn to survive.</p>
          <p>Each forest:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
            <li>rewards certain behaviors</li>
            <li>makes some questions feel dangerous</li>
            <li>renders some truths invisible</li>
            <li>causes certain fruit to feel <em>normal</em></li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            You don’t enter a forest because you’re foolish. You enter because it
            makes sense from the inside, especially when it has already trained your loves and fears.
          </p>
          <p>
            Most people will recognize more than one forest here. The point is not
            to pin yourself to a label, but to notice which climate has been shaping
            your instincts most deeply.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-black/10 dark:border-white/15" />

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black dark:text-white">
          What the Forests Reveal
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-base text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
          <p>The Forests are not mainly about having categories. They are about learning to witness truthfully.</p>
          <p>
            Each forest asks concrete questions. What does this world teach people to notice? What does it teach them to ignore? What fruit does it normalize? What quiet gospel does it preach? How might Christ expose and reorder it?
          </p>
          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-black/10 bg-white/60 p-5 text-sm text-neutral-700 dark:border-white/15 dark:bg-zinc-900/60 dark:text-neutral-300">
            Think of each forest as a formation climate: what it rewards, what it hides, and what kind of fruit starts to feel normal inside it.
          </div>
          <p>
            You do not need to master every forest. You need enough honesty to notice which one has been teaching you how to live, and enough patience to tell the truth without panic.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-black/10 dark:border-white/15" />

      <section class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black dark:text-white">
            The Forests
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-base text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
            Each forest below names a <strong>way the world trains us to see</strong>,
            often long before we realize how deeply we have started to trust it.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-base text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
            Enter slowly. Listen to the weather. Notice what feels familiar, persuasive, or strangely safe.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-4">
          {forestCards.map((forest) => (
            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-black/10 bg-white/70 p-6 shadow-sm dark:border-white/15 dark:bg-zinc-900/70">
              <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400">
                {forest.theme}
              </div>
              <div class="mt-2 text-lg font-semibold text-black dark:text-white">
                {forest.title}
              </div>
              <div class="mt-2 text-sm italic text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-400">
                {forest.tagline}
              </div>
              <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
                {forest.description}
              </p>
              {forest.href ? (
                <a
                  href={forest.href}
                  class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold text-black transition-colors duration-300 ease-in-out hover:text-black/70 dark:text-white dark:hover:text-white/70"
                >
                  Enter {forest.title} →
                </a>
              ) : (
                <div class="mt-4 text-sm font-semibold text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400">
                  Enter {forest.title} → <span class="text-xs uppercase">Coming Soon</span>
                </div>
              )}
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-black/10 dark:border-white/15" />

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black dark:text-white">
          Not Sure Where You Are?
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-base text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
          <p>You do not need to diagnose yourself to begin.</p>
          <p>
            <strong>The Clearing</strong> is a place to slow down, regain
            steadiness, and relearn how to tell the truth — without needing to defend a
            position or force a conclusion.
          </p>
          <p>
            It’s not an escape from the forest. It’s where you learn how to walk
            it wisely.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/the-clearing"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold text-black transition-colors duration-300 ease-in-out hover:text-black/70 dark:text-white dark:hover:text-white/70"
          >
            Go to The Clearing →
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-black/10 dark:border-white/15" />

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-black dark:text-white">
          A Gentle Word Before You Enter
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-base text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
          <p>
            You can live your entire life inside a forest and never realize it
            has borders.
          </p>
          <p>
            Leaving doesn’t always feel like freedom. Sometimes it feels like
            loss. Sometimes it feels like losing God — even when you’re learning
            to name the false gospel more truthfully.
          </p>
          <p>Take your time. No forest is left in a single step, and no person is reduced to a single forest.</p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </BottomLayout>
</PageLayout>
